The paper deals with the characterization of the capacity of a linear time-varying filter with additive white Gaussian noise, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The use of waterfilling in the time-frequency plane suggests that the paper may also be related to signal processing (cs.SP) and/or machine learning (cs.MM). The paper also discusses the rate distortion function for a nonstationary source, which could fall under the sub-category of statistical learning (cs.LG) or signal processing (cs.SP). Finally, the paper presents a proof of a specific Szego theorem, which is a topic in mathematical analysis and could be relevant to the sub-category of scientific computing (cs.SI).
